1
00:00:01,919 --> 00:00:04,129
[theme music plays]

2
00:01:23,177 --> 00:01:24,293
[intense music plays]

3
00:01:24,418 --> 00:01:26,292
I'm going to announce
my engagement to Light

4
00:01:26,378 --> 00:01:28,130
at the Pop Music Festival.

5
00:01:28,922 --> 00:01:31,174
I used to really like Kira too,

6
00:01:31,258 --> 00:01:33,969
but I know for sure
that Light is gonna catch him soon.

7
00:01:34,094 --> 00:01:35,387
[bangs the table, glass clatters]

8
00:01:35,554 --> 00:01:37,264
And as for you,
you'll probably be executed.

9
00:01:38,265 --> 00:01:41,602
You're to send me a fan letter
that I'll be able to recognize as yours.

10
00:01:41,768 --> 00:01:44,229
You will also enclose something else
in the envelope.

11
00:01:44,479 --> 00:01:46,356
Five blank pages from the notebook.

12
00:01:46,773 --> 00:01:48,900
Carry on with your judgements and killings
as usual

13
00:01:48,984 --> 00:01:51,320
until I receive the letter and the pages.

14
00:01:51,428 --> 00:01:52,988
[Mikami] And how about
after you receive them?

15
00:01:53,322 --> 00:01:56,199
[Takada] Make a notebook that looks
as close to the original as possible

16
00:01:56,617 --> 00:01:59,536
and act as if you're killing people
by using this decoy.

17
00:01:59,661 --> 00:02:01,121
[man] Oh, come on now, lady.

18
00:02:01,580 --> 00:02:03,790
I mean, wearing a short skirt like that
in the winter.

19
00:02:03,999 --> 00:02:05,375
Please, someone.

20
00:02:05,876 --> 00:02:06,835
[grunts]

21
00:02:10,672 --> 00:02:11,882
Delete…

22
00:02:12,215 --> 00:02:13,466
He's getting off the train.

23
00:02:13,553 --> 00:02:15,636
[woman screaming]

24
00:02:16,345 --> 00:02:17,638
[woman sobbing]

25
00:02:20,724 --> 00:02:23,644
VIGILANCE

26
00:02:24,353 --> 00:02:26,647
A man who was on the same train
as Mikami just collapsed.

27
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:29,483
He was harassing a young woman
and suddenly fell to the floor.

28
00:02:30,067 --> 00:02:33,403
It all happened about half a minute
after he wrote something in the notebook.

29
00:02:33,487 --> 00:02:34,780
That’s gotta be it.

30
00:02:35,489 --> 00:02:37,157
Well, now we know for sure.

31
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:38,155
X-KIRA
MIKAMI

32
00:02:38,259 --> 00:02:42,746
Yes. Our next order of business
is to get as close as possible to Mikami.

33
00:02:43,197 --> 00:02:44,790
But before we rush in blindly,

34
00:02:44,865 --> 00:02:46,625
there's something
we need to be careful of.

35
00:02:46,792 --> 00:02:49,878
And that…
is the being known as the Shinigami.

36
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:52,589
The Shinigami will be loyal to Mikami

37
00:02:52,964 --> 00:02:55,801
and will warn him if he discovers
we're following him.

38
00:02:56,593 --> 00:02:58,136
But the Shinigami can only be seen

39
00:02:58,212 --> 00:03:00,263
by those people
who have touched the notebook.

40
00:03:00,722 --> 00:03:01,933
It's going to be pretty difficult

41
00:03:02,008 --> 00:03:04,226
to be careful of something
we can't even see.

42
00:03:04,768 --> 00:03:07,062
[Near] We're gonna try,
no matter how difficult.

43
00:03:08,730 --> 00:03:09,898
Right. Understood, sir.

44
00:03:14,319 --> 00:03:15,862
[static noise]

45
00:03:17,656 --> 00:03:20,951
Light is having another one
of his meetings with Takada this evening.

46
00:03:21,785 --> 00:03:23,704
Right after they started having
these encounters,

47
00:03:23,912 --> 00:03:25,789
Takada got a phone call from Kira

48
00:03:26,194 --> 00:03:28,625
and all the surveillance cameras
had to be removed.

49
00:03:29,918 --> 00:03:31,670
The first thing that came to my mind

50
00:03:31,795 --> 00:03:33,880
was that they'd be able
to communicate secretly

51
00:03:33,945 --> 00:03:35,215
by writing messages.

52
00:03:35,674 --> 00:03:37,467
-Everything checks out in here.
-Huh?

53
00:03:37,968 --> 00:03:40,470
I've gone over the entire room
and there's nothing in it.

54
00:03:40,595 --> 00:03:42,472
There's only the wiretap on me.

55
00:03:43,014 --> 00:03:44,015
[Aizawa] Uh… right.

56
00:03:44,141 --> 00:03:45,851
Then all that's left is the bathroom.

57
00:03:50,573 --> 00:03:54,484
Why does Light care so much
about checking for cameras and wiretaps?

58
00:03:54,901 --> 00:03:55,944
Never mind that.

59
00:03:56,054 --> 00:03:59,114
Why is Kira allowing these meetings
in the first place?

60
00:03:59,406 --> 00:04:01,199
Something just doesn't add up.

61
00:04:02,868 --> 00:04:03,910
Hmm.

62
00:04:06,997 --> 00:04:09,291
If they really are
writing notes to each other,

63
00:04:09,541 --> 00:04:11,334
there's only one way to prove it.

64
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:19,926
Light, I thought you should know.

65
00:04:20,427 --> 00:04:23,237
I had a private chat
with Miss Misa Amane yesterday.

66
00:04:23,638 --> 00:04:24,681
[Light] About what?

67
00:04:24,931 --> 00:04:27,514
Whoa. Oh, boy! Light's in trouble now!

68
00:04:27,776 --> 00:04:30,604
Matsuda, is there some reason
you're so happy about this?

69
00:04:30,910 --> 00:04:33,571
She told me that she's planning
to announce her engagement to you

70
00:04:33,646 --> 00:04:35,609
during her appearance
at the Pop Music Festival.

71
00:04:35,859 --> 00:04:37,486
WHAT IS MISA TO YOU?

72
00:04:37,779 --> 00:04:40,155
Oh, he is busted. Light's in the doghouse!

73
00:04:40,255 --> 00:04:41,364
Shut up, Matsuda!

74
00:04:42,115 --> 00:04:43,700
No. She thinks we're together

75
00:04:43,784 --> 00:04:45,911
because I haven't been able
to break it to her yet.

76
00:04:46,081 --> 00:04:47,704
But she means nothing to me.

77
00:04:48,503 --> 00:04:50,081
Misa, you idiot.

78
00:04:50,290 --> 00:04:51,917
Why pull a stunt like that?

79
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,752
No, Takada. You're just as bad.

80
00:04:53,919 --> 00:04:56,505
Why are women like this? [grunts]

81
00:04:57,005 --> 00:04:58,194
Nothing, you say?

82
00:04:58,632 --> 00:04:59,966
Why should I believe you?

83
00:05:00,050 --> 00:05:00,965
[gasps]

84
00:05:02,505 --> 00:05:05,096
[Light's voice] She was
in charge of killing before T.

85
00:05:05,639 --> 00:05:08,141
Somehow, she gained
the same power as I had

86
00:05:08,391 --> 00:05:10,018
and found out that I was Kira.

87
00:05:10,393 --> 00:05:13,438
In the end, I had no choice
but to take her as my partner.

88
00:05:14,147 --> 00:05:17,680
It's the only reason I would ever choose
such an impulsive girl.

89
00:05:18,434 --> 00:05:20,954
[Takada] So, Misa was doing
Kira's killings.

90
00:05:21,152 --> 00:05:23,824
But right now,
I'm the one doing it for him.

91
00:05:24,533 --> 00:05:26,535
Light had no choice with Misa.

92
00:05:26,701 --> 00:05:29,162
But he chose me specially to help him.

93
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:32,290
Believe me, she's nothing.

94
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:34,709
You're the only one for me.

95
00:05:34,825 --> 00:05:36,378
"You're the only one for me?"

96
00:05:36,545 --> 00:05:37,963
Is that supposed to be serious?

97
00:05:38,171 --> 00:05:39,965
I expected better from you, Light.

98
00:05:40,131 --> 00:05:41,258
[Matsuda] She does have a point.

99
00:05:41,341 --> 00:05:43,937
-That's a pretty cheesy line for Light.
-[Light] Sorry. That's just how I feel.

100
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:45,595
[Ide] Do you think he will pick
Amane or Takada?

101
00:05:45,679 --> 00:05:47,514
[Takada] I wonder
how many women you've said that to?

102
00:05:47,597 --> 00:05:50,684
-[Matsuda] He could keep two-timing them.
-[Light] You think I'm that kind of guy?

103
00:05:50,809 --> 00:05:52,494
-[Ide] You don't see a problem with that?
-[growls]

104
00:05:52,544 --> 00:05:55,192
-[Matsuda] Hey, I'm not the one--
-Will you two shut up?

105
00:05:57,858 --> 00:06:00,318
You're going to have to
prove yourself from now on, Light.

106
00:06:00,569 --> 00:06:01,903
But I will trust you.

107
00:06:02,325 --> 00:06:05,782
Of course, if I find out
that you're lying, you'll pay dearly.

108
00:06:06,408 --> 00:06:08,952
In fact, I'll tell Kira about it.

109
00:06:09,062 --> 00:06:09,937
Hmm.

110
00:06:10,996 --> 00:06:12,080
Kira, huh?

111
00:06:12,622 --> 00:06:15,750
You know, I understand that the world
really needs Kira right now,

112
00:06:15,885 --> 00:06:18,003
but I just can't help but wonder,

113
00:06:18,545 --> 00:06:21,423
will the day ever come
when you and I can be together?

114
00:06:22,674 --> 00:06:25,719
I can't help but hate Kira
for choosing you as his spokesperson

115
00:06:25,806 --> 00:06:27,291
because it keeps us apart.

116
00:06:27,391 --> 00:06:28,972
I don't mind if he kills criminals,

117
00:06:29,055 --> 00:06:30,515
but we've done nothing wrong.

118
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:34,311
We have the right
to lead happy lives, don't we?

119
00:06:37,898 --> 00:06:40,984
"Yes, I want
to be happy together with you."

120
00:06:41,131 --> 00:06:43,236
"But that could only happen

121
00:06:43,570 --> 00:06:45,780
if Kira wasn't around."

122
00:06:46,530 --> 00:06:47,616
You're right.

123
00:06:47,741 --> 00:06:49,492
If only Kira wasn't around.

124
00:06:51,520 --> 00:06:52,553
"Kira

125
00:06:53,038 --> 00:06:54,456
should be arrested."

126
00:06:59,461 --> 00:07:00,420
It's true.

127
00:07:00,837 --> 00:07:02,923
If you and I are ever going
to have a chance

128
00:07:03,048 --> 00:07:04,174
of being happy together,

129
00:07:04,466 --> 00:07:05,926
Kira needs to be caught.

130
00:07:07,052 --> 00:07:08,428
Wait a minute, Kiyomi.

131
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:10,096
Do you seriously mean that?

132
00:07:10,221 --> 00:07:11,181
[Takada] Yes.

133
00:07:11,598 --> 00:07:12,557
[Light] All right.

134
00:07:12,641 --> 00:07:14,851
But if I'm going to arrest him,
I'll need your help.

135
00:07:14,976 --> 00:07:17,103
You'll be putting yourself in danger.

136
00:07:17,188 --> 00:07:18,939
[Light] After all,
I'll be defying the police,

137
00:07:19,038 --> 00:07:22,233
and you'll be going against Kira
and the entire world as well.

138
00:07:23,735 --> 00:07:24,945
Are you sure

139
00:07:25,654 --> 00:07:26,738
that's okay?

140
00:07:35,038 --> 00:07:36,873
That's a long pause.

141
00:07:39,876 --> 00:07:40,835
[Takada] All right.

142
00:07:41,586 --> 00:07:44,673
"If cooperating with you
means that we can be together,

143
00:07:44,881 --> 00:07:47,133
then I'm prepared
to make that sacrifice, Light."

144
00:07:47,258 --> 00:07:48,718
What a turnaround!

145
00:07:48,805 --> 00:07:50,345
Just like you'd expect from our guy!

146
00:07:50,595 --> 00:07:53,223
He was able to move the conversation
from cheating on Misa-Misa

147
00:07:53,306 --> 00:07:54,920
to getting Takki to help him!

148
00:07:58,561 --> 00:08:00,313
Mikami is talking to himself!

149
00:08:00,388 --> 00:08:01,348
What's going on?

150
00:08:01,481 --> 00:08:03,692
[Gevanni] He's too far away from me
to pick up his voice.

151
00:08:03,775 --> 00:08:05,735
But I recorded video of his lips moving.

152
00:08:06,987 --> 00:08:09,114
I'm sending you the footage
I was able to get.

153
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:10,782
It's of Mikami during his lunchbreak.

154
00:08:12,117 --> 00:08:14,202
This is it right here.
He's saying something.

155
00:08:14,536 --> 00:08:16,579
[Rester] Show it to us one more time
in slow motion.

156
00:08:25,588 --> 00:08:28,346
"Is that you, Shinigami?"

157
00:08:28,446 --> 00:08:29,471
is what he said.

158
00:08:30,927 --> 00:08:33,888
[Gevanni] He seems to have reacted
to the scrap of paper at his feet.

159
00:08:34,055 --> 00:08:35,932
[Rester] He just gave a small sigh.

160
00:08:36,558 --> 00:08:38,852
[Gevanni] At this point
he talks to himself a little more.

161
00:08:39,027 --> 00:08:40,570
I'm gonna zoom in on his lips.

162
00:08:42,731 --> 00:08:46,443
[Rester] That Shinigami.

163
00:08:46,985 --> 00:08:48,528
Ever

164
00:08:48,945 --> 00:08:49,904
since

165
00:08:50,091 --> 00:08:50,966
he…

166
00:08:52,449 --> 00:08:55,744
handed me the notebook…

167
00:08:57,434 --> 00:09:00,546
he hasn't reappeared.

168
00:09:01,082 --> 00:09:04,294
"That Shinigami. Ever since
he handed me the notebook,

169
00:09:04,361 --> 00:09:06,488
he hasn't reappeared."

170
00:09:08,715 --> 00:09:11,691
[Near] Mikami was given the notebook
by one of the Shinigami.

171
00:09:12,845 --> 00:09:15,638
But it seems that
Shinigami hasn't been following him.

172
00:09:18,391 --> 00:09:19,517
Hmm.

173
00:09:19,859 --> 00:09:21,186
So, that's how it is.

174
00:09:25,065 --> 00:09:26,566
I guess that's all for today.

175
00:09:26,816 --> 00:09:27,859
See you next time.

176
00:09:28,343 --> 00:09:29,386
Of course.

177
00:09:31,071 --> 00:09:33,698
[Matsuda] [grunting] It's finally over.

178
00:09:33,823 --> 00:09:35,992
Man, things got pretty intense today,
don't you think?

179
00:09:36,110 --> 00:09:38,076
It's tough to do this for hours on end.

180
00:09:38,389 --> 00:09:40,997
Yeah, you really look
like you're suffering.

181
00:09:41,414 --> 00:09:44,125
[Aizawa] All right. I'm gonna
wrap things up at the hotel.

182
00:09:44,601 --> 00:09:46,211
Okay. Thanks for all your hard work.

183
00:09:46,461 --> 00:09:48,268
You know, I feel kind of bad
that Aizawa is stuck

184
00:09:48,362 --> 00:09:50,463
with booking the hotel
and checking out every time.

185
00:10:14,989 --> 00:10:15,933
[gasps]

186
00:10:16,783 --> 00:10:17,867
It's gone.

187
00:10:18,326 --> 00:10:20,078
The mark I left is gone!

188
00:10:27,404 --> 00:10:28,320
[gasps]

189
00:10:30,088 --> 00:10:31,641
I left four marks.

190
00:10:31,925 --> 00:10:33,466
Two of them are gone.

191
00:10:34,279 --> 00:10:36,136
The room's been left just as it was.

192
00:10:36,419 --> 00:10:38,088
Housekeeping hasn't come in yet.

193
00:10:39,264 --> 00:10:43,768
Then how and why would anyone
switch these two notepads for new ones?

194
00:10:44,552 --> 00:10:45,845
That settles it.

195
00:10:46,604 --> 00:10:48,189
They're writing notes!

196
00:10:48,982 --> 00:10:50,268
-[phone ringing]
-Huh?

197
00:10:53,027 --> 00:10:54,070
Yes?

198
00:10:56,906 --> 00:10:57,866
What's that?

199
00:10:57,941 --> 00:11:00,485
You want to meet
and talk with Near in person?

200
00:11:07,834 --> 00:11:10,670
Mr. Aizawa, it's been a while.

201
00:11:11,421 --> 00:11:12,922
And it's a pleasure to meet you.

202
00:11:13,214 --> 00:11:14,549
That's very nice of you,

203
00:11:14,632 --> 00:11:16,975
but kinda hard to accept
while I'm blindfolded.

204
00:11:17,260 --> 00:11:19,637
He doesn't have
any weapons or cameras on him.

205
00:11:20,138 --> 00:11:22,682
In that case,
you're free to take off your blindfold.

206
00:11:24,554 --> 00:11:25,604
Hmm. [gasps]

207
00:11:30,099 --> 00:11:31,074
Near,

208
00:11:31,774 --> 00:11:33,484
I believe what you said earlier.

209
00:11:34,027 --> 00:11:36,529
L has been meeting Takada
almost every single night.

210
00:11:36,821 --> 00:11:38,239
-[Near] I know.
-Wha…?

211
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:40,491
Well, then what about this?

212
00:11:40,575 --> 00:11:42,285
They are passing notes to each other.

213
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:43,369
I confirmed it.

214
00:11:44,454 --> 00:11:45,872
[Near] Mr. Aizawa,

215
00:11:45,955 --> 00:11:48,499
please don't take any unnecessary actions
on your own.

216
00:11:48,791 --> 00:11:50,293
"Unnecessary actions?"

217
00:11:51,044 --> 00:11:52,754
[Near] Yes. This is not the point

218
00:11:52,837 --> 00:11:56,007
where we bring up evidence against Kira
and openly confront him.

219
00:11:56,591 --> 00:11:57,981
I must corner him in a dead end

220
00:11:58,092 --> 00:12:00,034
with a plan that
would guarantee his defeat.

221
00:12:00,303 --> 00:12:02,639
This is what it will take
to stop him for good.

222
00:12:03,306 --> 00:12:05,975
Mr. Aizawa,
I'm going to be blunt with you.

223
00:12:06,517 --> 00:12:09,103
You and the rest of the task force
are already out of the picture.

224
00:12:09,187 --> 00:12:10,114
[gasps]

225
00:12:12,023 --> 00:12:15,068
[Near] However, if you still want
to help capture Kira, you can.

226
00:12:15,276 --> 00:12:16,444
All I want you to do

227
00:12:16,531 --> 00:12:18,406
is keep an eye on him
as you've been doing.

228
00:12:19,405 --> 00:12:21,074
That's it? Keep an eye on him?

229
00:12:21,291 --> 00:12:22,201
Yes.

230
00:12:22,608 --> 00:12:23,726
Of course,

231
00:12:23,818 --> 00:12:26,371
there certainly is a purpose
in watching over L.

232
00:12:26,746 --> 00:12:28,706
In fact, I've already
taken it into account

233
00:12:28,781 --> 00:12:29,949
as a part of my plan.

234
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:32,919
That's why I'm hoping
you can help me in that respect.

235
00:12:33,002 --> 00:12:34,379
I want you to watch him.

236
00:12:34,712 --> 00:12:36,439
In order to win against Kira.

237
00:12:36,965 --> 00:12:38,216
And after that,

238
00:12:38,341 --> 00:12:39,955
I want you to be a witness

239
00:12:40,710 --> 00:12:42,253
to the end of Kira.

240
00:12:42,762 --> 00:12:43,712
[gasps]

241
00:13:03,700 --> 00:13:06,246
NHN HALL

242
00:13:06,346 --> 00:13:08,579
[Takada] This has been a year
of breakthroughs for me,

243
00:13:08,663 --> 00:13:10,373
and I'm sure for many others as well.

244
00:13:11,165 --> 00:13:13,876
And what better way to bring this year
to an exciting close

245
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:16,379
than with the East West
Pop Music Festival.

246
00:13:16,713 --> 00:13:19,424
I'm your host for this evening,
Kiyomi Takada.

247
00:13:19,757 --> 00:13:21,384
We hope you all enjoy the show.

248
00:13:21,843 --> 00:13:24,470
[Matsuda] All right.
The Pop Music Festival is about to begin!

249
00:13:24,595 --> 00:13:26,323
[Ide] Matsuda, shouldn't you be
checking over

250
00:13:26,373 --> 00:13:28,266
the reports on Kira's killings?

251
00:13:28,354 --> 00:13:30,598
Yeah, in a minute.
But after Misa-Misa performs.

252
00:13:30,673 --> 00:13:33,730
She's the opening act this year.
We gotta cheer her on. Yeah!

253
00:13:34,032 --> 00:13:34,973
[whimpers]

254
00:13:38,914 --> 00:13:40,705
[Misa] C-- Can we help you?

255
00:13:41,661 --> 00:13:43,226
-[door opens]
-Huh?

256
00:13:43,990 --> 00:13:46,492
Pardon me. We're from the SPK.

257
00:13:46,609 --> 00:13:47,938
We'll need you to come with us.

258
00:13:48,061 --> 00:13:49,031
[Misa whimpers]

259
00:13:51,497 --> 00:13:52,512
Before we continue,

260
00:13:52,566 --> 00:13:56,127
I'm afraid I must apologize
on behalf of the staff of NHN.

261
00:13:56,210 --> 00:13:57,587
It's very unfortunate,

262
00:13:57,668 --> 00:14:00,381
but it seems that this year's opening act
Miss Misa Amane

263
00:14:00,468 --> 00:14:02,258
has not entered the concert hall yet.

264
00:14:02,342 --> 00:14:03,760
-Huh?
-Huh?

265
00:14:03,843 --> 00:14:04,927
[Takada] Of course…

266
00:14:05,011 --> 00:14:06,814
-many unexpected things can…
-[Aizawa] What's going on?

267
00:14:06,889 --> 00:14:09,557
-Mogi didn't tell us anything about this.
-It's always full of surprises.

268
00:14:11,455 --> 00:14:14,093
[Misa] Take me back to NHN right now!

269
00:14:14,771 --> 00:14:16,402
What is this?!

270
00:14:16,477 --> 00:14:19,150
Are you trying to ruin my reputation?

271
00:14:19,279 --> 00:14:21,986
Misa-Misa, you've got to try
and stay calm.

272
00:14:22,070 --> 00:14:23,529
Mochi, why should I?

273
00:14:23,821 --> 00:14:25,990
[Mogi] We need to do this
in order to catch Kira.

274
00:14:26,115 --> 00:14:27,964
[Misa] But that has nothing to do with me!

275
00:14:28,409 --> 00:14:30,703
You should know that I was going
to take you at gunpoint

276
00:14:30,787 --> 00:14:31,746
as a last resort.

277
00:14:32,121 --> 00:14:33,539
But you didn't resist.

278
00:14:33,664 --> 00:14:36,167
That was a great help.
Thank you, Mr. Mogi.

279
00:14:36,292 --> 00:14:37,335
[Misa] Huh?

280
00:14:38,169 --> 00:14:39,504
[Mogi] I probably would have resisted

281
00:14:39,629 --> 00:14:41,654
if I hadn't listened
to what Aizawa told me. But…

282
00:14:43,049 --> 00:14:44,759
after hearing about the notepads,

283
00:14:44,926 --> 00:14:46,577
there’s no doubt in my mind.

284
00:14:48,477 --> 00:14:50,645
Hmm… What's going on?

285
00:14:52,333 --> 00:14:53,418
[Light] Near.

286
00:14:53,524 --> 00:14:55,017
[Near] Yes, what is it, L?

287
00:14:55,353 --> 00:14:56,437
[Light] We have a problem.

288
00:14:56,521 --> 00:14:58,606
Mogi and Misa Amane have gone missing.

289
00:14:58,940 --> 00:15:00,400
[Near] I'm already aware of that.

290
00:15:00,525 --> 00:15:02,318
I was the one who took them into custody.

291
00:15:02,402 --> 00:15:03,861
Uh! He what?

292
00:15:03,986 --> 00:15:05,071
For what reason?

293
00:15:05,947 --> 00:15:07,490
Oh, just in case.

294
00:15:10,326 --> 00:15:11,411
[Light] Near,

295
00:15:11,555 --> 00:15:13,913
kidnapping is a blatant criminal act.

296
00:15:14,055 --> 00:15:15,690
You have to stop this now.

297
00:15:15,790 --> 00:15:18,668
[Near] Actually, Mr. Mogi and Amane
both came here willingly.

298
00:15:18,762 --> 00:15:20,128
You can even ask them yourself.

299
00:15:20,588 --> 00:15:22,380
I'll put them on the line now.

300
00:15:22,588 --> 00:15:23,589
Here they are.

301
00:15:27,510 --> 00:15:30,555
-Mogi, Misa, this is L speaking.
-[Misa] Huh?

302
00:15:31,097 --> 00:15:32,181
[Misa] Light!

303
00:15:32,293 --> 00:15:34,308
[Light] I'm told
that Near is detaining you.

304
00:15:34,708 --> 00:15:37,520
He said that you both agreed to it.
Is that true?

305
00:15:40,731 --> 00:15:41,649
It is.

306
00:15:42,150 --> 00:15:43,234
[Aizawa] Mogi…

307
00:15:44,444 --> 00:15:46,988
Actually, I was against the whole thing.

308
00:15:47,196 --> 00:15:49,991
But Mochi said it would be best
if I just went along quietly.

309
00:15:50,116 --> 00:15:52,368
He told me we would have both
been killed if I didn't.

310
00:15:53,082 --> 00:15:54,132
[Light] All right.

311
00:15:54,286 --> 00:15:56,873
It's fine as long as you both
consented to this.

312
00:15:59,709 --> 00:16:01,794
So, now I've removed Misa Amane,

313
00:16:01,919 --> 00:16:04,494
the one who might be the Second Kira,
from the equation.

314
00:16:06,591 --> 00:16:07,842
Light Yagami,

315
00:16:08,087 --> 00:16:11,762
I'm sure the significance of this move
isn't lost on you.

316
00:16:13,347 --> 00:16:16,934
[man] No way! You're planning to end this
without Misa-Misa performing?!

317
00:16:17,018 --> 00:16:18,162
God, what a rip-off!

318
00:16:18,220 --> 00:16:20,271
[Gevanni] It looks like Lidner
and the others were successful.

319
00:16:20,573 --> 00:16:22,401
-[woman] Yeah!
-[man] We want our money back!

320
00:16:22,501 --> 00:16:23,691
[Gevanni] It's past nine.

321
00:16:23,941 --> 00:16:25,401
All right, it's my turn.

322
00:16:34,629 --> 00:16:35,529
[grunts]

323
00:16:40,191 --> 00:16:41,125
Hmm.

324
00:16:57,191 --> 00:16:59,560
Mikami leaves work
at almost the same time every day

325
00:16:59,644 --> 00:17:01,312
with only slight variations.

326
00:17:01,646 --> 00:17:04,190
He leads a completely scheduled life
for the most part.

327
00:17:04,859 --> 00:17:07,181
So, he always goes
to that particular gym

328
00:17:07,256 --> 00:17:09,438
every Monday and Thursday
at around nine o'clock.

329
00:17:09,513 --> 00:17:10,446
Is that correct?

330
00:17:10,571 --> 00:17:13,533
Yes. He's kept that routine
for the past four years,

331
00:17:13,616 --> 00:17:14,825
ever since he joined.

332
00:17:15,660 --> 00:17:17,330
He didn't even skip New Year's Day.

333
00:17:17,405 --> 00:17:19,214
I became a member
and made a few inquiries

334
00:17:19,289 --> 00:17:20,543
to confirm it myself.

335
00:17:21,415 --> 00:17:23,376
Good. So, then can we assume

336
00:17:23,793 --> 00:17:26,432
that he'll be there
on Monday the 31st as well?

337
00:17:26,529 --> 00:17:29,115
[Gevanni] Yes. If he's the type of man
who would go on holidays,

338
00:17:29,215 --> 00:17:31,133
then he'll certainly
go on New Year’s Eve.

339
00:17:32,468 --> 00:17:33,511
[Near] Gevanni.

340
00:17:33,636 --> 00:17:35,650
Would it be possible for you
to touch the notebook

341
00:17:35,725 --> 00:17:37,427
on the 31st at the gym?

342
00:17:38,266 --> 00:17:39,225
[gasps]

343
00:17:39,976 --> 00:17:41,018
Yes.

344
00:17:41,227 --> 00:17:43,980
I've already done a thorough check
of the hotel security.

345
00:17:44,188 --> 00:17:47,191
The locker room is definitely free
of any kind of surveillance.

346
00:17:47,483 --> 00:17:48,985
[Near] Then I'll leave it to you.

347
00:17:50,688 --> 00:17:52,823
Sir, if there is a Shinigami with him,

348
00:17:53,157 --> 00:17:55,992
there's a distinct possibility
that I will die, isn't there?

349
00:17:56,117 --> 00:17:57,243
[Near] Yes.

350
00:17:57,344 --> 00:17:59,913
Part of the reason you're doing this
is to test that theory.

351
00:18:00,425 --> 00:18:03,624
Even if you don't see any Shinigami
after first touching the notebook,

352
00:18:03,726 --> 00:18:06,294
I want you to continue
watching Mikami for a while longer

353
00:18:06,378 --> 00:18:08,963
before we conclude whether or not
he has one following him.

354
00:18:12,049 --> 00:18:14,428
I can have Rester do it
if you're too scared.

355
00:18:16,053 --> 00:18:17,346
No. I understand.

356
00:18:17,471 --> 00:18:18,431
I'll do it.

357
00:18:31,694 --> 00:18:32,820
Hmm.

358
00:18:33,154 --> 00:18:37,012
[heart beating loudly]

359
00:18:38,326 --> 00:18:39,952
[Gevanni]
If there's a Shinigami around--

360
00:18:40,131 --> 00:18:42,330
No, if there was one, I'd be dead.

361
00:18:42,413 --> 00:18:44,373
It's too late to turn back now.

362
00:18:44,607 --> 00:18:46,025
I have to touch it.

363
00:18:46,709 --> 00:18:49,063
[heartbeat getting louder]

364
00:19:06,562 --> 00:19:08,606
[gasping]

365
00:19:11,944 --> 00:19:13,227
[sighs]

366
00:19:15,571 --> 00:19:17,740
Sir, I've succeeded
in touching the notebook.

367
00:19:18,157 --> 00:19:20,159
I can't confirm the existence
of any Shinigami

368
00:19:20,242 --> 00:19:21,243
at this time.

369
00:19:22,528 --> 00:19:23,654
[Near] Commander Rester,

370
00:19:23,752 --> 00:19:25,873
please connect me with Mr. Mogi
for a moment.

371
00:19:26,540 --> 00:19:27,583
[Misa] Huh?

372
00:19:27,958 --> 00:19:29,126
Mr. Mogi.

373
00:19:29,251 --> 00:19:31,587
According to your investigation
on the rules of the notebook,

374
00:19:31,712 --> 00:19:34,298
how long can a person
be controlled before their death?

375
00:19:35,758 --> 00:19:38,302
Based on the data
we got from Yotsuba's experiments,

376
00:19:38,418 --> 00:19:39,679
it's 23 days.

377
00:19:40,096 --> 00:19:41,263
[Near] Are you sure?

378
00:19:41,389 --> 00:19:42,361
Yes.

379
00:19:42,436 --> 00:19:45,768
I'd say that the killings done by Yotsuba
were more than enough to prove it.

380
00:19:46,310 --> 00:19:47,937
[Near] Thank you for your assistance.

381
00:19:49,438 --> 00:19:51,524
We have to consider the possibility

382
00:19:51,607 --> 00:19:53,901
that Gevanni is already being controlled.

383
00:19:53,980 --> 00:19:57,279
In that case, they could be making him
say that there is no Shinigami.

384
00:19:57,809 --> 00:20:02,076
That means I need to confront L
in exactly 24 days…

385
00:20:02,284 --> 00:20:04,704
if Gevanni is still alive until then.

386
00:20:05,338 --> 00:20:06,383
[Rester grunts]

387
00:20:07,873 --> 00:20:10,543
JANUARY 3

388
00:20:10,626 --> 00:20:13,587
[Light] Kiyomi, I saw you had some trouble
at the Pop Music Festival.

389
00:20:14,340 --> 00:20:17,874
Yes. I never imagined
that Miss Amane would go missing.

390
00:20:18,592 --> 00:20:20,594
[Light's voice]
"Give T an order to contact you

391
00:20:20,678 --> 00:20:22,805
and let you know as soon
as he's confirmed everything."

392
00:20:23,431 --> 00:20:24,682
"Once you hear from him,

393
00:20:24,765 --> 00:20:27,893
I want you to send me a text message
or call me with the following message,

394
00:20:28,144 --> 00:20:30,396
'I want to see you as soon as possible'".

395
00:20:30,813 --> 00:20:33,315
JANUARY 6

396
00:20:36,444 --> 00:20:37,528
[Rester] Photographs?

397
00:20:37,820 --> 00:20:38,696
[Near] Yes.

398
00:20:38,863 --> 00:20:41,326
I want to see exactly
what he wrote in the notebook.

399
00:20:42,533 --> 00:20:45,327
I want to see the pattern
in how Mikami writes,

400
00:20:45,578 --> 00:20:46,912
if there are any habits,

401
00:20:47,037 --> 00:20:49,123
and what kind of notebook it is.

402
00:20:49,262 --> 00:20:50,708
I wanna see it all.

403
00:20:50,833 --> 00:20:53,043
Everything in detail,
with my own eyes.

404
00:20:53,304 --> 00:20:56,788
[camera shutter clicking]

405
00:20:57,029 --> 00:20:58,843
[mysterious music plays]

406
00:21:02,303 --> 00:21:03,179
[grunts]

407
00:21:08,934 --> 00:21:10,227
[Rester] What do you think, Near?

408
00:21:10,519 --> 00:21:13,564
[Near] Perfect.
Gevanni has done an excellent job.

409
00:21:14,100 --> 00:21:17,693
The handwriting matches that
of the records Mikami keeps as prosecutor.

410
00:21:18,027 --> 00:21:19,480
There's absolutely no doubt.

411
00:21:19,558 --> 00:21:20,905
This is his handwriting.

412
00:21:21,030 --> 00:21:21,947
[Rester] I agree.

413
00:21:22,436 --> 00:21:24,239
With this, we can do it.

414
00:21:26,660 --> 00:21:33,584
TO BE CONTINUED

415
00:21:35,878 --> 00:21:39,122
[theme music plays]
